WEBVTT

00:02.883 --> 00:04.175
[ SIREN WAILS ]
Arizona:
UNCONTROLLABLE BLEEDING.

00:04.175 --> 00:05.716
ACIDOSIS.

00:05.716 --> 00:07.338
COLD.

00:07.338 --> 00:10.221
WE ALL KNOW
WHAT THE COMBINATION MEANS.

00:10.221 --> 00:13.013
[ FLATLINE ]
WE CALL IT THE TRIAD OF DEATH,

00:13.013 --> 00:15.806
THE POINT OF NO RETURN.

00:17.348 --> 00:19.810
WE'VE BEEN TALKING ABOUT HAVING
ANOTHER BABY FOR MONTHS!

00:19.810 --> 00:22.193
WE WERE EXCITED! WE WERE
DISCUSSING FREAKING NAMES!

00:22.193 --> 00:23.904
WHY WOULD YOU DO THAT --
JUST TO GET MY HOPES UP?

00:23.904 --> 00:25.276
YOU'RE ATTACKING ME
FOR SOMETHING

00:25.276 --> 00:28.028
THAT I NEVER EVEN SAID!
YOU DIDN'T HAVE TO SAY
ANYTHING!

00:28.028 --> 00:30.411
IT'S CLEAR FROM EVERYTHING
THAT YOU DO THAT
YOU DON'T WANT THIS.

00:30.411 --> 00:32.203
WHY START TRAINING
ALL OVER AGAIN?

00:32.203 --> 00:34.034
YOU'RE AN AMAZING
PEDIATRIC SURGEON.

00:34.034 --> 00:35.956
PEOPLE CROSS THE COUNTRY JUST TO
HAVE YOU OPERATE ON THEIR KIDS.

00:35.956 --> 00:37.158
FOR THE LAST TIME,

00:37.158 --> 00:38.829
THE FELLOWSHIP IS ADVANCING
MY CAREER, WHICH IS --

00:38.829 --> 00:40.711
WHICH IS NOT ADVANCING
THIS FAMILY!

00:40.711 --> 00:42.833
IT'S THE MOMENT IN THE O.R.

00:42.833 --> 00:44.425
WHEN YOU TURN
TO DAMAGE CONTROL.

00:44.425 --> 00:46.837
CALLIE, ACTUALLY,
IF I COULD STOP YOU THERE,

00:46.837 --> 00:49.470
I'M INTERESTED TO HEAR THE REST
OF ARIZONA'S SENTENCE.

00:49.470 --> 00:52.012
ARIZONA,
YOU WERE GOING TO SAY...?

00:52.012 --> 00:53.844
YOU STOP.

00:53.844 --> 00:55.936
YOU STEP BACK.

00:55.936 --> 00:59.980
YOU LET THE BODY REST AND SEE
IF YOU CAN FIND A SOLUTION...

00:59.980 --> 01:02.103
TO THE CHAOS
THAT'S HAPPENING INSIDE.

01:02.103 --> 01:03.944
COURTNEY,
YOU'RE DOING GREAT.
CLAMP.

01:03.944 --> 01:05.526
IS SHE OKAY?
TELL ME SHE'S OKAY.

01:05.526 --> 01:07.688
ARE YOU KIDDING?
SHE'S ABSOLUTELY BEAUTIFUL.

01:07.688 --> 01:09.570
ISN'T THAT RIGHT, ROBBINS?
SHE'S SO BEAUTIFUL.

01:09.570 --> 01:11.902
WE'RE JUST GONNA CHECK HER OUT
AND GET HER A LITTLE OXYGEN.

01:11.902 --> 01:14.365
Dr. Herman: LAP PADS.

01:14.365 --> 01:17.368
ALL RIGHT, THE PLACENTA,
ROBBINS.
YEAH, I GOT IT.

01:17.368 --> 01:18.959
UH, HEY, ALEX,
HOW ARE HER SATS?

01:18.959 --> 01:20.371
Alex: BELOW 90,
BUT IMPROVING WITH BAGGING.

01:20.371 --> 01:21.502
ALL RIGHT,
LET'S GET HER READY TO GO.

01:21.502 --> 01:23.164
ROBBINS, THE BABY
IS NO LONGER YOUR PATIENT.

01:23.164 --> 01:24.255
PAY ATTENTION HERE.

01:26.417 --> 01:27.918
[ ALARMS BEEPING ]

01:27.918 --> 01:30.801
ARIZONA, YOU READY?
[ THUNDER RUMBLING ]

01:30.801 --> 01:34.925
UM...
[CLEARS THROAT]

01:35.926 --> 01:39.930
I LOVE WHEN YOU TALK
TO A PATIENT

01:39.930 --> 01:41.772
AND IT'S LIKE THEY'RE THE ONLY
PERSON IN THE WHOLE WORLD.

01:41.772 --> 01:46.106
I LOVE, UM, YOU BITE YOUR LIP
JUST A TEENY BIT --

01:46.106 --> 01:47.898
IT'S BARELY NOTICEABLE --
WHEN YOU STUDY SCANS,

01:47.898 --> 01:50.361
AND I FIND IT
REALLY SEXY.

01:50.361 --> 01:53.194
I LOVE WHEN YOU DO
THE VOICES

01:53.194 --> 01:56.287
WHEN YOU READ TO SOFIA AT NIGHT
[Laughing] AND MAKE HER LAUGH

01:56.287 --> 02:01.081
AND I COULD LISTEN
TO THAT SOUND ALL DAY...

02:01.081 --> 02:02.873
FOR THE REST OF MY LIFE.

02:02.873 --> 02:08.419
AND YOU SMILE WHEN YOU SLEEP --
LIKE, BIG, LIKE, CRAZY-BIG.

02:08.419 --> 02:10.050
[ SIGHS ]
AND I LOVE THAT WHEN I WAKE UP,

02:10.050 --> 02:11.422
THAT'S THE FIRST THING
I SEE.

02:11.422 --> 02:13.924
[ SIGHS ]
UH, AND I LOVE --

02:13.924 --> 02:16.387
[ Voice breaking ] SEE, WHY --
WHY DON'T YOU JUST -- GOD.

02:16.387 --> 02:18.219
[ SIGHS ]

02:18.219 --> 02:20.891
CALLIE, DO YOU WANT TO
TALK ABOUT HOW ARIZONA'S
WORDS MAKE YOU FEEL?

02:20.891 --> 02:24.855
UM, WELL, IT'S JUST --
I JUST -- I -- I -- [SIGHS]

02:24.855 --> 02:27.818
IF YOU'D SAY THIS STUFF OUT LOUD
ONCE IN A WHILE.

02:27.818 --> 02:29.860
I WOULD [CHUCKLES]
IF YOU'D LET ME.

02:29.860 --> 02:32.863
WAIT, WHAT?
I WAS JUST SAYING THEM RIGHT
NOW, AND THEN YOU CUT ME OFF,

02:32.863 --> 02:35.035
I MEAN, YOU'RE TOO BUSY
TRYING TO SPEAK FOR ME --

02:35.035 --> 02:36.947
OKAY,
REMEMBER THE LANGUAGE

02:36.947 --> 02:38.329
WE TALKED ABOUT USING
WITH EACH OTHER.

02:40.831 --> 02:43.334
I FEEL THAT
YOU'RE ALWAYS CUTTING --

02:43.334 --> 02:45.206
WELL, I FEEL THAT
YOU'RE CONSTANTLY
ACCUSING ME OF THIS --

02:45.206 --> 02:46.877
I FEEL YOU DID THAT
AGAIN.

02:46.877 --> 02:49.089
SHE JUST DID IT AGAIN!
LET'S TRY AGAIN.

02:49.089 --> 02:51.051
[ SIGHS ]

02:51.051 --> 02:52.843
CALLIE, I FEEL, UH,

02:52.843 --> 02:54.054
THAT YOU SHOULD GO
WITH A PRIMARY REPAIR.

02:54.054 --> 02:56.056
EH, I FEEL THE ARTERY'S MISSING
TOO LARGE A PIECE.

02:56.056 --> 02:57.428
WE'LL DO
AN INTERPOSITION GRAFT.

02:57.428 --> 02:58.849
W-- YOU AGREED WITH ME
IN PRE-OP.

02:58.849 --> 03:00.681
YEAH, WELL, I CHANGED MY MIND
ONCE I GOT IN HERE

03:00.681 --> 03:01.972
AND SAW THE EXTENT
OF THE DEFECT.

03:01.972 --> 03:03.934
UM, FINISHED LIGATING
THE BLEEDERS,

03:03.934 --> 03:05.266
SO WE'RE
ALL SET UP HERE.

03:05.266 --> 03:07.898
YEAH, AND I DON'T SEE
ANY MORE BONE FRAGMENTS,
DR. TORRES, SO --

03:07.898 --> 03:09.810
WHEN YOU SO QUICKLY DISREGARD
MY MEDICAL OPINION,

03:09.810 --> 03:12.943
IT MAKES ME FEEL LIKE YOU FORGET
THAT I'M A PEDIATRIC SURGEON

03:12.943 --> 03:14.154
WHO KNOWS
THAT INTERPOSITIONAL GRAFTS

03:14.154 --> 03:15.576
CAN CAUSE COMPLICATIONS
IN CHILDREN.

03:15.576 --> 03:17.117
WELL, WHEN YOU QUESTION ME
IN THE O.R.,

03:17.117 --> 03:19.029
IT MAKES ME FEEL LIKE
YOU DON'T THINK I CAN DO MY JOB.

03:19.029 --> 03:21.031
WE'LL USE A PTFE GRAFT,
WILSON.
USE THE GREAT SAPHENOUS VEIN,
WILSON.

03:21.031 --> 03:22.913
WE DON'T NEED
ANY SYNTHETIC MATERIALS.
[ SCOFFS ]

03:22.913 --> 03:24.665
OKAY, FINE,
CUT INTO THE KID'S LEG.

03:25.666 --> 03:28.589
[ ALARMS BEEPING ]

03:28.589 --> 03:29.880
Arizona:
IT'S NOT ABOUT THE LEG.

03:29.880 --> 03:32.833
IT WAS NEVER ABOUT THE --
IT GOES WAY BEFORE THE LEG.

03:32.833 --> 03:37.468
FOUR YEARS AGO, I RECEIVED
THE GRANT OF A LIFETIME.

03:37.468 --> 03:39.300
GOING TO AFRICA,
WORKING IN THAT CLINIC --

03:39.300 --> 03:41.682
THAT WAS AN OPPORTUNITY THAT I
NEVER THOUGHT THAT I WOULD GET.

03:41.682 --> 03:42.973
YOU FOLLOWED YOUR DREAM.
YOU WENT.

03:42.973 --> 03:44.054
BUT YOU WERE SUPPOSED
TO GO WITH ME,

03:44.054 --> 03:45.556
AND YOU WERE MISERABLE

03:45.556 --> 03:46.807
AND LETTING EVERYONE KNOW
ABOUT IT.

03:46.807 --> 03:47.978
AND SO I WENT.
I WENT WITHOUT YOU,

03:47.978 --> 03:50.271
AND THEN I CAME BACK --
FOR YOU.

03:50.271 --> 03:51.692
I CAME BACK FOR YOU.

03:51.692 --> 03:54.615
AND WHEN I CAME BACK,
YOU WERE --
PREGNANT?

03:57.858 --> 03:59.029
I'M BISEXUAL.

03:59.029 --> 04:00.951
I'M ATTRACTED TO BOTH MEN AND
WOMEN, AND IT FREAKS HER OUT.

04:00.951 --> 04:02.953
YES, I SLEPT WITH MARK.
I GOT PREGNANT.

04:02.953 --> 04:06.076
I WAS PREGNANT. AND?

04:06.076 --> 04:08.499
AND I HAD NO TIME
TO PROCESS IT.

04:08.499 --> 04:09.830
I WAS SO IN LOVE WITH YOU,

04:09.830 --> 04:12.583
I JUST WANTED TO BE WITH YOU,
NO MATTER WHAT.

04:12.583 --> 04:13.924
AND I-IF IN ORDER
TO BE WITH YOU --

04:13.924 --> 04:15.796
IF YOU'RE ABOUT TO SAY WHAT
I THINK YOU'RE ABOUT TO SAY --

04:15.796 --> 04:16.967
LET ME GET A WORD IN,
CALLIE!

04:16.967 --> 04:18.589
I TRAPPED YOU INTO A KID,

04:18.589 --> 04:21.261
A KID YOU NEVER WANTED,
AND NOW YOU'RE STUCK.

04:21.261 --> 04:24.975
DON'T YOU EVER SAY

04:24.975 --> 04:27.808
THAT I DON'T LOVE MY CHILD
OR THAT I REGRET MY CHILD!

04:27.808 --> 04:30.020
I REGRET THAT YOU MADE
A DECISION FOR ME!

04:30.020 --> 04:32.192
YOU MAKE
ALL THE CHOICES!

04:32.192 --> 04:34.395
AND EVERY TIME THAT I TRY
TO MAKE A DECISION FOR MYSELF,

04:34.395 --> 04:35.776
IT'S LIKE
YOU MAKE ME FEEL LIKE

04:35.776 --> 04:37.988
THE WORST, MOST SELFISH PERSON
IN THE WHOLE WORLD!

04:37.988 --> 04:38.949
I'M SORRY.

04:38.949 --> 04:40.160
DID I MAKE YOU FEEL SELFISH

04:40.160 --> 04:41.992
WHEN YOU DECIDED TO SLEEP
WITH ANOTHER WOMAN?

04:43.033 --> 04:43.994
[ SIGHS ]

04:43.994 --> 04:46.667
I'M SO SORRY.
THAT'S NOT WHAT I MEANT,

04:46.667 --> 04:48.619
AND YOU KNOW
THAT'S NOT WHAT I MEANT.

04:48.619 --> 04:51.672
I MEANT THAT ANYTIME THAT I TRY
AND DO SOMETHING FOR MYSELF,

04:51.672 --> 04:54.335
YOU -- YOU -- J--

04:54.335 --> 04:57.588
Dawson: CALLIE,
THE SESSION'S NOT DONE YET.

04:57.588 --> 05:00.010
IT FEELS PRETTY DONE.

05:00.010 --> 05:01.342
NO!

05:01.342 --> 05:02.973
THAT'S THE STUPIDEST IDEA
I'VE EVER HEARD.

05:02.973 --> 05:04.805
IT IS NOT A STUPID IDEA.
SHE DIDN'T MEAN "STUPID."

05:04.805 --> 05:06.266
SHE JUST SAID
THE WORD "STUPID," SO --

05:06.266 --> 05:07.307
Callie:
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT SPENDING

05:07.307 --> 05:09.229
A LARGE PORTION
OF MY GRANT MONEY

05:09.229 --> 05:12.022
ON A COMPLICATED
STAGED FACIAL RECONSTRUCTION

05:12.022 --> 05:13.313
FOR ONE PATIENT.

05:13.313 --> 05:15.025
SO, WHAT, YOU WANT
TO JUST REJECT HIM?

05:15.025 --> 05:17.738
NO, WE FIND A WAY TO HELP HIM
THAT'S LESS STUPID!

05:17.738 --> 05:20.070
OKAY, I'M GONNA GRAB LUNCH.
HUNT, FIND ME LATER.

05:20.070 --> 05:22.613
[ SIGHS ]

05:25.536 --> 05:26.997
HOW'S IT GOING, HUH?

05:28.949 --> 05:32.753
IT'S JUST I KEEP GIVING
AND GIVING AND GIVING.

05:32.753 --> 05:34.625
YOU'RE GIVING ME
THINGS I DIDN'T ASK FOR, CALLIE.

05:34.625 --> 05:35.876
Callie:
THAT IS NOT TRUE!

05:35.876 --> 05:37.918
ALL I'VE DONE IS EVERYTHING
THAT YOU'VE ASKED ME TO DO.

05:37.918 --> 05:40.761
YOU ASKED ME TO NOT LEAVE YOU
AFTER THE PLANE CRASH. I DIDN'T.

05:40.761 --> 05:42.803
YOU WANTED ME TO STAY
AFTER YOU CHEATED ON ME. I DID.

05:42.803 --> 05:44.925
THEN YOU WANTED A HOUSE.
WE GOT IT.

05:44.925 --> 05:48.729
I DO EVERYTHING FOR YOU,
ARIZONA, BECAUSE I LOVE YOU.
I LOVE YOU, TOO!

05:48.729 --> 05:50.851
WELL, AND NOW WE'RE HERE,
AND I WANT SOMETHING,

05:50.851 --> 05:52.813
AND YOU CAN'T GIVE IT TO ME.
YOU WON'T GIVE IT TO ME.

05:52.813 --> 05:54.935
I NEVER SAID
THAT I DIDN'T WANT A BABY!

05:54.935 --> 05:56.397
THE WHOLE REASON
THAT WE'RE HERE

05:56.397 --> 05:58.238
IS BECAUSE OF YOU
AND WHAT YOU WANT.

05:58.238 --> 06:00.531
I AM TRYING TO GIVE YOU
WHAT YOU WANT,

06:00.531 --> 06:01.572
BUT YOU MAKE IT SO HARD.

06:01.572 --> 06:02.903
WHY CAN'T YOU COMMIT
TO ANYTHING?

06:02.903 --> 06:04.865
I'VE COMMITTED THE PAST
FIVE YEARS OF MY LIFE TO YOU.

06:06.487 --> 06:09.410
WE'RE...NOT
GETTING ANYWHERE.

06:09.410 --> 06:12.703
[ SIGHS ]
WE'VE CIRCLED RIGHT BACK
TO WHERE WE STARTED.

06:12.703 --> 06:14.334
IT MAY BE TIME TO HIT
THE RESET BUTTON.

06:14.334 --> 06:16.757
GREAT.
LET'S -- LET'S RESET.

06:16.757 --> 06:17.918
HOW?

06:17.918 --> 06:20.801
HAVE YOU EVER CONSIDERED
SPENDING SOME TIME APART?

06:20.801 --> 06:22.423
BECAUSE A BREAK
CAN ACTUALLY --

06:22.423 --> 06:23.804
YOU MEAN A SEPARATION?
NO.

06:23.804 --> 06:25.135
WE'RE TRYING TO SAVE
OUR MARRIAGE, NOT DESTROY IT.

06:25.135 --> 06:27.177
I DON'T WANT TO DO THAT.
LET HER FINISH.

06:27.177 --> 06:28.809
Dawson: DON'T THINK OF IT
AS A SEPARATION.

06:28.809 --> 06:30.601
YOU TWO HAVE GONE THROUGH
SO MUCH.

06:30.601 --> 06:31.932
YOU'RE COMPLETELY
DIFFERENT PEOPLE

06:31.932 --> 06:33.474
THAN WHEN YOU FIRST
GOT TOGETHER.

06:33.474 --> 06:36.016
IT CAN BE HELPFUL
TO REDISCOVER WHO YOU ARE,

06:36.016 --> 06:37.858
TAKE A BREAK
FROM ONE ANOTHER.

06:37.858 --> 06:39.900
BREAK, SEPARATION --
IT'S THE SAME THING.

06:39.900 --> 06:41.692
IT'S THE FIRST STEP
TO DIVORCE.

06:41.692 --> 06:43.574
IS THIS WHAT YOU WANT?
IS THIS WHAT YOU --
LET HER FINISH.

06:43.574 --> 06:45.946
LOOK, IN MY EXPERIENCE,
COUPLES COME TO THERAPY

06:45.946 --> 06:47.578
FOR ONE OF TWO REASONS.

06:47.578 --> 06:49.289
EITHER ONE PERSON WANTS OUT
OF THE RELATIONSHIP

06:49.289 --> 06:51.411
AND THEY NEED HELP
TELLING THE OTHER,

06:51.411 --> 06:53.994
OR THEY BOTH DESPERATELY WANT
TO MAKE IT WORK.

06:53.994 --> 06:55.496
THEY WANT TO FIGHT
TO MAKE IT WORK.

06:55.496 --> 06:57.377
WELL, WE WANT
TO MAKE IT WORK, RIGHT?

06:57.377 --> 06:58.919
RIGHT. RIGHT.

06:58.919 --> 07:00.711
AND A BREAK
IS NOT AN END.

07:00.711 --> 07:02.422
A BREAK IS A TOOL
TO HELP MAKE IT WORK,

07:02.422 --> 07:04.134
FOR AN AGREED-UPON TIME,

07:04.134 --> 07:06.847
AND THEN WE COME TOGETHER,
RE-EVALUATE THE RELATIONSHIP.

07:06.847 --> 07:08.679
NO. I DON'T LIKE IT.
I DON'T -- NO.

07:08.679 --> 07:10.931
I THINK IT'S CRAZY.
I'M SORRY, I DO.

07:10.931 --> 07:12.392
I-I MEAN, WE'RE SUPPOSED
TO BE GETTING CLOSER,

07:12.392 --> 07:13.604
SO, WHAT,
WE NEED MORE SPACE?

07:13.604 --> 07:15.686
NO, WE NEED MORE TIME TOGETHER,
NOT APART.

07:15.686 --> 07:18.018
THAT'S HOW YOU MAKE THINGS WORK,
RIGHT?

07:18.018 --> 07:20.731
NO BREAK, RIGHT?

07:23.564 --> 07:26.156
I THINK WE SHOULD TAKE
A BREAK.

07:40.460 --> 07:41.712
HOW LONG -- HOW LONG
WILL THE BREAK LAST?

07:41.712 --> 07:43.463
AS LONG AS YOU'D LIKE.
WE DECIDE THAT NOW.

07:43.463 --> 07:47.007
OKAY. UM...30 DAYS?

07:47.007 --> 07:49.219
30 DAYS? A MONTH?

07:49.219 --> 07:51.802
YOU NEED A BREAK FROM ME
FOR A WHOLE MONTH?

07:51.802 --> 07:55.686
ARIZONA, YOU WANT TO SAY
SOMETHING, NOW IS THE TIME.

07:55.686 --> 07:57.267
CALLIE,
I WAS TRYING TO BE NICE.

07:57.267 --> 07:59.269
I-I DON'T EVEN THINK
THAT THAT'D BE ENOUGH.

07:59.269 --> 08:00.981
I MEAN,
IF I THOUGHT YOU'D GO FOR IT,

08:00.981 --> 08:03.734
MAYBE THREE MONTHS,
SIX MONTHS.

08:03.734 --> 08:05.816
OH -- OH, MY GOD.
SIX MONTHS?

08:05.816 --> 08:07.067
I'M TRYING TO BE HONEST.

08:07.067 --> 08:08.989
I WANT TO SAVE US,
BUT THE ONLY WAY THAT I KNOW

08:08.989 --> 08:10.370
HOW TO DO THIS IS
BY BEING HONEST.

08:10.370 --> 08:12.533
THIS FEELS LIKE A JOKE.

08:12.533 --> 08:14.244
OR A REALITY SHOW.

08:14.244 --> 08:16.166
"REAL LESBIAN HOUSEWIVES M.D.
OF SEATTLE."

08:23.083 --> 08:25.836
FINE, 30 DAYS.
HOW DOES IT WORK? [ SIGHS ]

08:25.836 --> 08:28.799
YOU HAVE A CHILD,
SO FOR HER SAKE,

08:28.799 --> 08:30.801
YOU TWO WILL LIVE IN THE HOUSE
AS PARENTS,

08:30.801 --> 08:33.844
BUT WITH SEPARATE LIVES,
SEPARATE ROOMS.

08:33.844 --> 08:35.896
BOUNDARIES ARE VITAL.

08:35.896 --> 08:38.268
MAKE A SCHEDULE
FOR CHILD-CARE RESPONSIBILITIES,

08:38.268 --> 08:39.519
AND STICK TO IT.

08:39.519 --> 08:41.902
NO TALKING,

08:41.902 --> 08:46.196
NO COMMUNICATION,
EXCEPT IN EMERGENCIES.

08:46.196 --> 08:48.739
LASTLY --
THIS IS IMPORTANT...

08:48.739 --> 08:49.910
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

08:49.910 --> 08:52.863
...NO INTIMACY, NO SEX,

08:52.863 --> 08:56.917
WITH OTHER PEOPLE
OR WITH EACH OTHER.

08:56.917 --> 09:00.210
[ DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE ]

09:00.210 --> 09:04.124
[ SIGHS ]

09:04.124 --> 09:07.467
SOFIA'S GETTING DRESSED.

09:07.467 --> 09:09.129
SHE ALSO SEEMS
TO BE CONTINUING

09:09.129 --> 09:11.261
THE PURPLE THEME
SHE'S GOT GOING ON THIS WEEK.

09:15.936 --> 09:18.979
ARIZONA,
I DIDN'T SLEEP AT ALL.

09:18.979 --> 09:20.771
I CAN'T DO THIS.

09:20.771 --> 09:22.983
IT'S BEEN ONE NIGHT,
AND, UM...

09:22.983 --> 09:26.777
I FEEL WE DON'T NEED THIS.

09:26.777 --> 09:29.860
HOW ARE WE SERIOUSLY SUPPOSED TO
NOT TALK FOR AN ENTIRE MONTH?

09:33.694 --> 09:36.747
JUST -- PLEASE, JUST PLEASE LOOK
AT ME. I NEED TO TALK.

09:36.747 --> 09:38.619
[ SIGHS ]

09:38.619 --> 09:39.910
[ SIGHS ]

09:52.012 --> 09:54.054
EMILY, I'M SORRY.
I KNOW IT HURTS.

09:54.054 --> 09:56.596
HURTS LIKE A BITCH.
YEAH,
MEDS WILL KICK IN SOON.

09:56.596 --> 09:58.018
YOU GOT YOUR ARM CAUGHT
IN WHAT, AGAIN?

09:58.018 --> 10:00.851
A NOODLE-MAKING MACHINE.
HUH.

10:00.851 --> 10:03.984
IT'S THE DUMBEST JOB EVER,
BUT IT JUST PAYS WELL,

10:03.984 --> 10:06.026
AND I'M TRYING TO GET
INTO CULINARY SCHOOL,

10:06.026 --> 10:07.397
WHICH IS
FREAKING EXPENSIVE.

10:07.397 --> 10:08.819
Stephanie: LOOKS LIKE
COMMINUTED, DISPLACED

10:08.819 --> 10:11.571
MID-SHAFT RADIUS
AND ULNA FRACTURES.
YEP.

10:11.571 --> 10:12.943
WELL, EMILY,

10:12.943 --> 10:15.575
UNFORTUNATELY, YOUR ARM
DEFINITELY NEEDS SURGERY.

10:15.575 --> 10:17.367
NOW, IN ORDER TO STABILIZE
THE FRACTURE,

10:17.367 --> 10:19.790
I WILL MOST LIKELY NEED TO PUT
IN A PLATE AND SOME SCREWS.

10:19.790 --> 10:21.872
UH, EDWARDS,
CALL UP TO THE O.R.

10:21.872 --> 10:23.243
HOW LONG WILL IT TAKE
TO HEAL?

10:23.243 --> 10:25.916
I NEED MY ARM IN SHAPE TO COOK,
TO TRAIN FOR SCHOOL.

10:25.916 --> 10:27.668
APPLICATIONS ARE DUE
IN A MONTH.

10:27.668 --> 10:29.629
WELL, OBVIOUSLY,
IT'S A PRETTY BAD FRACTURE,

10:29.629 --> 10:30.841
BUT WE WILL FIX YOU UP,

10:30.841 --> 10:32.422
WE WILL GET YOU INTO P.T.
AS SOON AS WE CAN,

10:32.422 --> 10:34.885
AND YOU WILL BE BACK AT IT
BEFORE YOU KNOW IT, OKAY?

10:34.885 --> 10:37.017
ALL RIGHT.

10:37.017 --> 10:38.679
[ SIGHS ]

10:38.679 --> 10:41.762
Jo:
LEE FRANKLIN, ONE DAY OLD,

10:41.762 --> 10:43.814
DIAGNOSED WITH
ESOPHAGEAL ATRESIA AT BIRTH.

10:43.814 --> 10:45.816
WHICH MEANS
THAT HIS ESOPHAGUS

10:45.816 --> 10:46.977
DEVELOPED
IN TWO SEPARATE PIECES.

10:46.977 --> 10:48.979
I'M SORRY, BUT I THOUGHT YOU
SAID YOU COULD FIX THE GAP.

10:48.979 --> 10:50.030
WHEN IS THAT GONNA HAPPEN?

10:50.030 --> 10:52.232
WELL, UNFORTUNATELY,
LEE'S IMAGES SHOW

10:52.232 --> 10:53.774
A LONGER GAP
THAN WE PREDICTED.

10:53.774 --> 10:56.576
IT'S MEASURING AROUND FOUR
CENTIMETERS, WHICH PREVENTS US

10:56.576 --> 10:58.368
FROM SIMPLY SEWING THE TWO ENDS
BACK TOGETHER.

10:58.368 --> 10:59.780
DR. KAREV
CAN STILL OPERATE.

10:59.780 --> 11:01.661
IT JUST MAKES THE SURGERY
A LITTLE BIT MORE COMPLICATED.

11:01.661 --> 11:02.913
WILSON?

11:02.913 --> 11:06.837
WE'LL ATTACH SUTURES TO BOTH
ENDS OF LEE'S ESOPHAGUS,

11:06.837 --> 11:08.999
THREADING THEM OUT THROUGH
INCISIONS IN HIS BACK.

11:08.999 --> 11:11.211
EVERY DAY,
WE'LL PULL ON THE SUTURES,

11:11.211 --> 11:14.004
THEREBY STRETCHING THE ENDS
INSIDE TOWARD EACH OTHER

11:14.004 --> 11:16.636
IN ORDER TO CONNECT THEM
IN A LATER SURGERY.

11:16.636 --> 11:18.889
HOWEVER,
FOR THE PROCEDURE TO WORK,

11:18.889 --> 11:21.101
WE'LL NEED LEE TO REMAIN
EXTREMELY STILL,

11:21.101 --> 11:23.223
SO WE'LL NEED TO PUT HIM
IN A MEDICALLY INDUCED COMA.

11:23.223 --> 11:25.565
I-I'M SORRY,
BUT, DR. ROBBINS,

11:25.565 --> 11:26.897
BUT W-WHY AREN'T YOU DOING
THE SURGERY?

11:26.897 --> 11:29.019
DR. KAREV IS NOW THE ATTENDING
ON THIS CASE.

11:29.019 --> 11:30.771
I HAVE RECENTLY STARTED
A NEW SPECIALTY

11:30.771 --> 11:32.022
IN A DIFFERENT DEPARTMENT.

11:32.022 --> 11:33.653
BUT I CAN ASSURE YOU,

11:33.653 --> 11:36.026
I TRAINED DR. KAREV,
AND HE IS AWESOME.

11:36.026 --> 11:38.989
Y-YOU HAVE TO PUT OUR BABY
INTO A COMA?

11:38.989 --> 11:40.660
FOR HOW LONG?

11:40.660 --> 11:43.123
THIS PROCESS COULD TAKE...
WEEKS.

11:43.123 --> 11:44.995
THERE ARE OTHER SURGICAL OPTIONS
I'D LOVE TO GO OVER --

11:44.995 --> 11:47.918
BUT THIS IS THE BEST ONE
FOR LEE.

11:47.918 --> 11:48.959
DR. ROBBINS,
CAN I SEE YOU OUTSIDE?

11:51.631 --> 11:52.672
WHAT WAS THAT?

11:52.672 --> 11:53.964
YOU'RE JUST GONNA
MAKE THEM WORRY.

11:53.964 --> 11:55.796
I WAS THINKING OF DOING
A COLONIC INTERPOSITION.

11:55.796 --> 11:58.218
I FIX THE KID IN ONE SURGERY,
HE CAN GO HOME SOONER.

11:58.218 --> 12:00.010
NO, USING THE NATIVE ESOPHAGUS
IS BETTER.

12:00.010 --> 12:02.142
IT'S A PROLONGED HOSPITAL STAY,
BUT --
[ SIGHS ]

12:02.142 --> 12:04.895
WE COULD HAVE HIM IN A COMA
FOR WEEKS, MAYBE MONTHS.

12:04.895 --> 12:06.807
I MEAN, THAT'LL PUT THE PARENTS
THROUGH HELL.

12:06.807 --> 12:08.979
USING THE COLON HAS
INCREASED RISKS OF STRICTURE,

12:08.979 --> 12:10.901
ANASTOMOTIC LEAKS, GERD.
[ CELLPHONE CHIMES ]

12:10.901 --> 12:12.562
I MEAN, IT'S NOT FUN
TO WATCH YOUR KID GO
THROUGH THAT, EITHER.

12:12.562 --> 12:15.065
ARE YOU GONNA LET ME DO MY
JOB, OR ARE YOU GONNA DO
IT FOR ME THE WHOLE TIME?

12:15.065 --> 12:16.236
OH, CRAP,
I'M LATE FOR ROUNDS.

12:16.236 --> 12:17.697
OKAY, LISTEN,
JUST DO IT MY WAY, OKAY?

12:17.697 --> 12:19.159
FINE, ONLY BECAUSE
HE WAS ONCE YOUR PATIENT

12:19.159 --> 12:20.991
AND BECAUSE YOU'RE HAVING
TROUBLE CUTTING THE STRINGS.

12:20.991 --> 12:22.993
YEAH, OR BECAUSE
YOU KNOW THAT I'M RIGHT.

12:22.993 --> 12:25.035
Woman:
HERE YOU GO, DOCTOR.

12:25.035 --> 12:26.787
THANKS.

12:26.787 --> 12:28.959
Dr. Herman: I SENT YOUR HUSBAND
DOWN TO THE GIFT SHOP.

12:28.959 --> 12:30.921
HE FAINTED LAST TIME
WE TALKED ABOUT NEEDLES.

12:30.921 --> 12:32.542
OH, HE'S
SUCH A LIGHTWEIGHT.

12:32.542 --> 12:34.925
WELL, HOPEFULLY,
HE'S BUYING YOU SOME CHOCOLATE.

12:34.925 --> 12:36.006
YOU'RE LATE.

12:36.006 --> 12:38.218
I'M SO SORRY. UH, I WAS CHECKING
ON A BABY IN THE NICU --

12:38.218 --> 12:40.430
DON'T CARE.
GRAHAM, START TALKING.

12:40.430 --> 12:42.512
JACLYN WERLEIN,
23 WEEKS ALONG --

12:42.512 --> 12:44.554
RECENT FETAL ECHO
OF HER BABY'S HEART

12:44.554 --> 12:46.386
UNFORTUNATELY CONFIRMED
CRITICAL AORTIC STENOSIS.

12:46.386 --> 12:49.019
TODAY, WE'LL BE PERFORMING
A FETAL AORTIC VALVULOPLASTY

12:49.019 --> 12:51.151
IN ORDER TO OPEN UP
THE NARROWED AORTIC VALVE.

12:51.151 --> 12:53.483
YOUR B.P'.s A LITTLE HIGH.
YOU FEELING OKAY?

12:53.483 --> 12:55.105
[ SIGHS ]
I'M A LITTLE NERVOUS.

12:55.105 --> 12:56.897
THE IDEA OF A GIANT NEEDLE
GOING THROUGH ME

12:56.897 --> 12:59.199
AND THEN
MY BABY'S TEENY HEART --

12:59.199 --> 13:01.071
THERE DOESN'T SEEM TO BE
MUCH ROOM FOR ERROR.

13:01.071 --> 13:03.824
DR. HERMAN HAS MADE US
THE GO-TO HOSPITAL

13:03.824 --> 13:05.075
FOR FETAL CARDIAC
INTERVENTION.

13:05.075 --> 13:07.407
SHE IS THE ONLY SURGEON
WHO EVEN DOES THIS PROCEDURE

13:07.407 --> 13:08.708
IN THE PACIFIC NORTHWEST.

13:08.708 --> 13:11.581
SHE'S WHY I'M HERE --
TO LEARN FROM HER.

13:11.581 --> 13:14.464
JACLYN, I'M NOT EVEN
GOING TO INSERT THE NEEDLE

13:14.464 --> 13:17.257
UNTIL I'M SURE YOUR BABY'S
IN THE PRECISE POSITION

13:17.257 --> 13:19.089
THAT HE NEEDS TO BE.
OKAY.

13:19.089 --> 13:21.301
Dr. Herman: POSITION IS CRITICAL
TO SUCCESS.

13:21.301 --> 13:23.884
IF THE FETUS ISN'T
FACING FORWARD, CHEST UP,

13:23.884 --> 13:25.805
WE CAN'T GET TO THE APEX
OF THE HEART.

13:25.805 --> 13:27.307
PERFECT APPROACH,
GRAHAM.

13:27.307 --> 13:28.849
WE HAVE DIRECT ACCESS NOW.

13:28.849 --> 13:30.931
I'VE BEEN PRACTICING
IN THE LAB.

13:30.931 --> 13:33.353
DR. HERMAN,
I'D BE HAPPY TO ASSIST.

13:33.353 --> 13:35.815
GRAHAM IS ASSISTING ON THIS ONE.
WATCH. TAKE NOTES.

13:35.815 --> 13:37.567
I'VE PERFORMED DOZENS

13:37.567 --> 13:38.818
OF PERCUTANEOUS PROCEDURES
ON BABIES.

13:38.818 --> 13:40.861
WERE THE BABIES
STILL IN UTERO?

13:40.861 --> 13:42.652
DID THEY HAVE HEARTS
THE SIZE OF A WALNUT?

13:42.652 --> 13:44.034
NO. NO, BUT --

13:44.034 --> 13:45.495
WELL, THAT'S NOT THE SAME,
THEN, IS IT?

13:45.495 --> 13:48.408
ROBBINS,
YOU HAVE AN IMPECCABLE RECORD

13:48.408 --> 13:50.160
AS A PEDIATRIC SURGEON.

13:50.160 --> 13:52.622
AS A FETAL SURGEON,
BIG, FAT ZERO.

13:52.622 --> 13:57.007
I SUGGEST YOU PAY CLOSE
ATTENTION TO GRAHAM'S HANDS,

13:57.007 --> 13:58.588
AND NEXT TIME,
YOU CAN ASSIST.

13:58.588 --> 14:01.801
WELL, DR. HERMAN, MY HANDS ARE
ONLY TRYING TO EMULATE YOURS.

14:01.801 --> 14:04.965
GRAHAM, ONE MORE WORD,
WE'RE GONNA GO OVER TO PLASTICS

14:04.965 --> 14:07.467
AND HAVE YOUR LIPS SURGICALLY
REMOVED FROM MY ASS.

14:08.468 --> 14:11.231
NOW, SHUT UP, EVERYONE.
I'M DEPLOYING THE BALLOON.

14:14.604 --> 14:16.476
OH, [SNAPS FINGERS]
IN CASE YOU'RE INTERESTED,

14:16.476 --> 14:18.818
THERE'S A MODEL YOU CAN
PRACTICE ON IN THE SKILLS LAB.

14:18.818 --> 14:20.440
IT'S OLD,
AND THE RUBBER'S HARDENED,

14:20.440 --> 14:22.943
AND IT SMELLS GROSS,
BUT HAVE FUN.

14:22.943 --> 14:25.075
THANKS.
IT TOOK ME ABOUT TWO MONTHS
TO NAIL IT.

14:25.075 --> 14:26.196
GOOD LUCK.

14:29.449 --> 14:31.161
OH, EDWARDS, HEY.

14:31.161 --> 14:33.163
UM, ARE YOU STILL ON
CALLIE'S SERVICE?

14:33.163 --> 14:34.794
NO, THIS IS
THE FOURTH TIME

14:34.794 --> 14:36.917
THAT SHE HAS SWITCHED SOFIA DUTY
ON ME.

14:36.917 --> 14:38.258
SHE SAID
SHE HAD TO PRACTICE.

14:38.258 --> 14:39.709
YOU TELL HER
THAT HER DAUGHTER'S ASKING

14:39.709 --> 14:40.880
WHEN SHE'S GONNA TUCK HER IN
AT NIGHT,

14:40.880 --> 14:43.003
AND REMIND HER
THAT WE SHARE CUSTODY

14:43.003 --> 14:44.965
IN THIS
STUPID ARRANGEMENT.
OKAY, THIS REALLY ISN'T

14:44.965 --> 14:46.967
SOMETHING
THAT I FEEL COMFORTABLE --
GET OUT, EDWARDS.

14:50.390 --> 14:51.811
[ Sighing ] OH, SORRY.

14:51.811 --> 14:54.474
YOU WERE SAYING, UH,
THYROID CANCER?

14:54.474 --> 14:56.186
PATIENT IS DAVID LASHER.

14:56.186 --> 14:58.148
I DID A THYROIDECTOMY
ON HIM,

14:58.148 --> 15:00.360
AND SINCE THEN,
HE HAS BEEN CANCER-FREE,

15:00.360 --> 15:02.822
BUT THIS MORNING, HE CAME IN
COMPLAINING OF HIP PAIN,

15:02.822 --> 15:04.654
SO I DID A PET SCAN,
AND --

15:04.654 --> 15:05.825
BONE METS TO THE HIP.

15:05.825 --> 15:07.117
IS THERE ANY WAY
TO RESECT THIS

15:07.117 --> 15:08.658
WITHOUT DOING
A TOTAL HIP REPLACEMENT?

15:08.658 --> 15:10.910
NO, IT LOOKS LIKE IT INVOLVES
TOO MUCH OF THE PROXIMAL FEMUR.

15:10.910 --> 15:14.124
HOW OLD IS DAVID?
33, TWO KIDS AND A WIFE.

15:14.124 --> 15:16.536
HOW LONG
WILL A REPLACEMENT LAST?

15:16.536 --> 15:18.208
UH, 10, 15 YEARS.

15:18.208 --> 15:20.500
SO HE'LL NEED ANOTHER ONE
EVENTUALLY.

15:20.500 --> 15:23.003
WELL, YEAH, BUT WE EITHER RESECT
IT AND DO A TOTAL HIP NOW,

15:23.003 --> 15:25.135
OR HIS CANCER CONTINUES
TO SPREAD, AND HE DIES.

15:25.135 --> 15:26.926
WELL, IT LOOKS LIKE

15:26.926 --> 15:28.308
I'M SCHEDULING
A HIP REPLACEMENT.

15:28.308 --> 15:29.889
YEAH. OH, NO.

15:29.889 --> 15:31.851
DON'T -- DON'T SCHEDULE IT NOW.
I HAVE A --

15:31.851 --> 15:33.013
A KID TO PICK UP.

15:33.013 --> 15:35.435
AND YOU HAVE TO KEEP ON A SMILE
ON YOUR FACE

15:35.435 --> 15:37.557
DESPITE YOUR SPOUSE
BARELY SPEAKING TO YOU.

15:37.557 --> 15:38.818
TOTALLY GET THAT.

15:38.818 --> 15:40.270
[ SIGHS ]

15:43.903 --> 15:46.066
GOOD NIGHT.
[ CHUCKLES ]

15:46.066 --> 15:48.238
SWEET DREAMS.

15:49.990 --> 15:52.993
[ SIGHS ]
OKAY.

15:52.993 --> 15:56.036
[ ARIZONA LAUGHS ]

15:56.036 --> 15:59.459
I HAD TO LOOK AT SO MANY PLACES
TO FIND THIS, BUT I DID.

15:59.459 --> 16:00.790
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

16:00.790 --> 16:01.791
HEY, CALLIE.

16:03.133 --> 16:04.794
ARE WE TOO LOUD
FOR SOFIA?

16:04.794 --> 16:06.466
NO, I JUST PUT HER DOWN.
I THOUGHT Y--

16:08.428 --> 16:09.759
I THOUGHT ARIZONA
HAD TO STUDY.

16:12.432 --> 16:15.265
RIGHT, UH, TALKING IS AGAINST
THE RULES.

16:15.265 --> 16:17.647
SORRY.
YES, ARIZONA IS STUDYING.

16:17.647 --> 16:19.809
I AM HELPING HER MAKE
JELLO MOMS TO PRACTICE ON.

16:19.809 --> 16:21.691
THE JELLO IS THE UTERUS,

16:21.691 --> 16:23.023
AND THE GRAPES --
TINY, LITTLE BABY HEARTS.

16:23.023 --> 16:24.604
IT'S THE PERFECT
SURGICAL MODEL.

16:24.604 --> 16:27.197
YOU GO IN RIGHT HERE,
AND --
NEAT.

16:27.197 --> 16:30.110
I'M ALSO MAKING
AMBROSIA SALAD --

16:30.110 --> 16:31.411
KEPNER FAMILY RECIPE.

16:37.537 --> 16:39.919
Dawson:
SO, THEN WHAT DID YOU DO?

16:41.421 --> 16:44.384
I FOLLOWED THE RULES.

16:44.384 --> 16:45.465
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

16:45.465 --> 16:47.797
YOUR RULES, BY THE WAY --
THEY SUCK.

16:57.517 --> 16:58.938
Dr. Herman:
OKAY, ALMOST THERE.

16:58.938 --> 17:03.063
JUST MOVE THE BABY'S
LEFT SHOULDER DOWN, DOWN.

17:03.063 --> 17:05.855
OKAY. THAT'S GOOD.
CONGRATULATIONS, ROBBINS.

17:05.855 --> 17:08.027
THAT WAS THE FASTEST
I'VE EVER SEEN ANYONE

17:08.027 --> 17:09.359
FLIP A FETUS INTO POSITION.

17:09.359 --> 17:10.410
THANK YOU, DR. HERMAN.

17:10.410 --> 17:11.821
SO, ONCE WE GET
THE NEEDLE IN,

17:11.821 --> 17:13.323
YOU WANT TO DO THE REST
OF THE PROCEDURE?

17:13.323 --> 17:15.285
[ Laughing ] YES.

17:15.285 --> 17:17.367
Arizona: BUT I'M NOT --
I'M NOT SURE I SHOULD.

17:17.367 --> 17:19.289
I'VE ONLY PRACTICED A COUPLE
TIMES IN THE SKILLS LAB,

17:19.289 --> 17:21.000
AND I-I DON'T KNOW
IF I'M THERE YET.

17:21.000 --> 17:23.293
WELL, I'M HAPPY TO ASSIST
IF SHE'S NOT READY.

17:23.293 --> 17:26.376
GRAHAM, I WANT YOU TO
TAKE SPECIAL NOTE OF
WHAT ROBBINS DID THERE.

17:26.376 --> 17:27.717
OH, YES, MA'AM.

17:27.717 --> 17:28.968
I-I-I SAW IT.

17:28.968 --> 17:31.010
THAT'S WHAT BEING AN EXPERIENCED
SURGEON GAINS YOU --

17:31.010 --> 17:33.263
THE WISDOM TO KNOW
YOUR LIMITATIONS.

17:33.263 --> 17:34.804
SHE'S NOT GONNA LET
HER OWN ARROGANCE

17:34.804 --> 17:36.096
GET IN THE WAY
OF PATIENT CARE.

17:36.096 --> 17:37.137
GOOD CALL, ROBBINS.

17:37.137 --> 17:39.179
NICE WORK, GUYS.

17:39.179 --> 17:41.561
ROBBINS, YOU'LL TAKE THE LEAD
ON THE NEXT ONE. BE READY.

17:41.561 --> 17:43.523
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]
OF COURSE, DR. HERMAN.

17:43.523 --> 17:46.776
[ LAUGHS ] YES!

17:46.776 --> 17:48.898
[ GROANS ]
OH, EMILY,
I NEED YOU TO REMAIN STILL.

17:48.898 --> 17:51.401
I THOUGHT THE SURGERY
WAS SUPPOSED TO FIX IT!

17:51.401 --> 17:55.365
IT STILL HURTS, ALMOST WORSE
THAN WHEN IT GOT CAUGHT!

17:55.365 --> 17:57.787
OKAY, WELL, YOU'RE A LITTLE
OVER A WEEK POST-OP, EMILY.

17:57.787 --> 17:59.329
IT'S STILL GONNA HURT FROM
TIME TO TIME. EDWARDS, LABS?

17:59.329 --> 18:00.870
HER BLOOD WORK'S
COMPLETELY NORMAL.

18:00.870 --> 18:02.202
UH, THE INCISION
LOOKS GOOD --

18:02.202 --> 18:04.464
NO SIGN OF INFECTION,
NO COMPARTMENT SYNDROME.

18:04.464 --> 18:07.167
I CAN'T SLEEP.
I CAN'T EAT. OH!

18:07.167 --> 18:09.129
OKAY. OKAY.

18:09.129 --> 18:12.302
I GET THESE SHOCKS LIKE
TWO OR THREE TIMES A MINUTE,

18:12.302 --> 18:14.304
AND I -- I CAN'T DO IT,
DR. TORRES.

18:16.516 --> 18:19.139
EMILY, I AM SO SORRY.
I-I'VE RUN EVERY TEST.

18:19.139 --> 18:20.890
NOTHING'S COMING UP.

18:20.890 --> 18:22.932
I'M NOT SURE WHAT I CAN DO.
SOMETHING!

18:22.932 --> 18:24.934
GOT TO DO SOMETHING
TO HELP ME.

18:24.934 --> 18:27.026
I CAN'T LIVE LIKE THIS.

18:27.026 --> 18:29.489
IF I HAD KNOWN
IT WAS GONNA BE LIKE THIS...

18:29.489 --> 18:32.492
[ SOBBING ]

18:32.492 --> 18:33.783
PLEASE.

18:42.412 --> 18:43.203
WHOA.

18:43.203 --> 18:44.954
SORRY.

18:44.954 --> 18:46.796
YOU'RE GOOD?
YOU OKAY?

18:46.796 --> 18:48.127
AM I GOOD?

18:48.127 --> 18:50.250
I AM OBVIOUSLY NOT GOOD.
I'M OBVIOUSLY NOT OKAY.

18:50.250 --> 18:52.011
WHY WOULD YOU ASK THAT
IF YOU ALREADY KNOW THE ANSWER?

18:52.011 --> 18:54.013
WHY NOT TRY,
"WHAT IS IT, CALLIE?"

18:54.013 --> 18:56.466
"WHAT CAN I DO, CALLIE,"
LIKE A HUMAN PERSON?

18:56.466 --> 18:58.308
SORRY.
I HAVE MY OWN STUFF.

18:58.308 --> 19:00.930
NO, I'M S--
[ SIGHS ]

19:00.930 --> 19:02.562
I'M SORRY.
IT'S MY FAULT.

19:02.562 --> 19:06.936
I JUST...I HAVE NO ONE
TO TALK TO.

19:08.768 --> 19:11.441
YOU ON CALL RIGHT NOW?
NO, WHY?

19:12.692 --> 19:14.864
TWO MORE.
IT'S CALLED
AN IN-HOME SEPARATION.

19:14.864 --> 19:17.036
WE LIVE IN THE SAME HOUSE.

19:17.036 --> 19:18.908
WE TRADE OFF
CARING FOR SOFIA.

19:18.908 --> 19:20.119
WE JUST CAN'T TALK
OR HAVE SEX.

19:20.119 --> 19:21.951
EXACTLY WHAT DEREK AND I
ARE DOING, ONLY HEALTHY.

19:21.951 --> 19:24.664
OH.
WELL, CHEERS TO THAT.

19:25.915 --> 19:27.046
GOOD MAN IN THE STORM.

19:27.046 --> 19:28.588
WHAT'S SO "GOOD MAN
IN THE STORM" ABOUT A BREAK?

19:28.588 --> 19:29.879
"HOW WAS YOUR DAY,
MEREDITH?

19:29.879 --> 19:31.170
"DID YOU CURE DEATH TODAY,
MEREDITH?

19:31.170 --> 19:32.552
WHEN ARE YOU GONNA CURE DEATH,
MEREDITH?"

19:32.552 --> 19:33.923
OH, GOD.
"I COULD HAVE CURED DEATH

19:33.923 --> 19:36.005
IF YOU LET ME MOVE TO D.C.
AND WORK FOR THE PRESIDENT."

19:36.005 --> 19:37.797
SO I'M BISEXUAL!
SO WHAT?

19:37.797 --> 19:40.300
IT'S A THING,
AND IT'S REAL.

19:40.300 --> 19:44.183
I MEAN [CHUCKLES]
IT'S CALLED LGBTQ FOR A REASON.

19:44.183 --> 19:46.606
THERE'S A "B" IN THERE,
AND IT DOESN'T MEAN "BADASS."

19:46.606 --> 19:48.938
OKAY, IT KIND OF DOES,
BUT IT ALSO MEANS BI.

19:50.109 --> 19:51.150
[ LAUGHS ]

19:51.150 --> 19:52.232
MM.

19:52.232 --> 19:53.943
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]
MM.

19:53.943 --> 19:56.906
MY MOM AND THE CHIEF WERE
DOING IT ALL OVER THE HOSPITAL.

19:56.906 --> 19:58.948
MNH-MNH.
ALL OVER THE HOSPITAL,

19:58.948 --> 20:01.581
LIKE ME AND DEREK --
CHEATING ON ADDISON.

20:01.581 --> 20:03.493
I'M A LEGACY CHEATER.
MM.

20:03.493 --> 20:05.665
MAYBE SOFIA WILL BE
A LEGACY CHEATER.

20:05.665 --> 20:07.707
EVERYONE IN THIS HOSPITAL'S
CHEATED ON ME.

20:07.707 --> 20:11.501
EVERY SINGLE PERSON I HAVE EVER
MARRIED HAS CHEATED ON ME --

20:11.501 --> 20:14.003
ALL, UH, TWO OF THEM?

20:14.003 --> 20:14.964
YEAH.

20:14.964 --> 20:16.716
COME ON.

20:18.928 --> 20:20.890
CRISTINA WAS THE THIRD RAIL
IN OUR MARRIAGE --

20:20.890 --> 20:23.973
DANGEROUS, FULLY CHARGED,
COULD KILL US,

20:23.973 --> 20:25.725
BUT NECESSARY FOR US
TO KEEP GOING.

20:25.725 --> 20:27.056
SHE GOT ME.

20:27.056 --> 20:28.898
YOU THINK IT'S POSSIBLE

20:28.898 --> 20:30.900
THAT MY ONE TRUE LOVE IN MY LIFE
IS A GIRL?

20:30.900 --> 20:33.653
DID YOU GET EXCITED
BY HER VAGINA?

20:33.653 --> 20:34.944
NO.

20:34.944 --> 20:35.945
THEN NO.

20:35.945 --> 20:38.658
GOOD POINT.

20:38.658 --> 20:40.320
♪ VAGINA ♪

20:40.320 --> 20:42.492
♪ VA-VA-VA ♪
♪ VAGINA ♪

20:42.492 --> 20:43.623
SING IT.

20:43.623 --> 20:44.784
♪ VA-VA-VAGINA ♪
♪ VAGINA ♪

20:44.784 --> 20:46.956
♪ VAGI-NA-HA ♪
IT'S A WEIRD WORD.

20:46.956 --> 20:49.579
I THINK IT SOUNDS PRETTY.
PEOPLE SHOULD SAY IT MORE.

20:49.579 --> 20:51.581
OH, GOD, I MISS SEX.

20:51.581 --> 20:53.503
I'M HOT.
MY HUSBAND'S AN IDIOT.

20:55.295 --> 20:58.177
DO IT.
[ CHUCKLES ]

21:00.009 --> 21:02.342
THAT MIGHT COME BACK UP.
[ GRUNTS ]

21:25.865 --> 21:27.997
[ DOOR CREAKS ]

21:33.333 --> 21:35.675
MM.

22:14.123 --> 22:17.006
[ ALARMS BEEPING ]

22:17.006 --> 22:18.087
SO, YOU BROKE THE RULES.

22:18.087 --> 22:19.549
NO. NO, WE STOPPED.

22:19.549 --> 22:20.800
WE DIDN'T HAVE SEX.

22:20.800 --> 22:23.553
WE J-- WE JUST -- WE KISSED
AND, UH, SOMEHOW STOPPED.

22:23.553 --> 22:25.885
I MEAN, SHE'D HAD
THAT BIG SURGERY WITH
DR. HERMAN THAT DAY,

22:25.885 --> 22:29.929
AND ALL I WANTED TO DO WAS
ASK HER HOW IT WENT.

22:29.929 --> 22:32.141
WE DIDN'T HAVE SEX.

22:32.141 --> 22:33.853
CLOSE ENOUGH.

22:33.853 --> 22:36.315
WELL, NOW I WISH THAT
WE HADN'T STOPPED. SO, UH...

22:36.315 --> 22:38.478
[ SIGHS ]
SO, WHAT HAPPENS NOW?

22:38.478 --> 22:39.859
IN ORDER FOR THIS TO WORK,

22:39.859 --> 22:41.821
YOU HAVE TO FOLLOW THE RULES
FOR THE FULL 30 DAYS.

22:41.821 --> 22:44.484
YOU DON'T MEAN...

22:44.484 --> 22:46.826
[ ALARMS BEEPING ]

22:51.491 --> 22:53.372
WHEN ARE YOU PLANNING ON
DOING THE ANASTOMOSIS?

22:53.372 --> 22:55.915
ENDS WILL BE CLOSE ENOUGH
TO JOIN IN A DAY OR TWO.

22:55.915 --> 22:57.877
LATEST GAPOGRAM SHOWS
WE'RE ALMOST THERE.

22:57.877 --> 22:59.419
HOW MUCH ARE YOU PULLING
EACH DAY?

22:59.419 --> 23:01.421
UH, ABOUT TWO MILLIMETERS.

23:01.421 --> 23:02.712
OH. ONE'S SAFER.

23:02.712 --> 23:04.003
WHY ARE YOU UP HERE AGAIN?

23:04.003 --> 23:06.636
[ SCOFFS ]
DO YOU EVEN KNOW WHAT I'M DOING?

23:06.636 --> 23:08.928
I AM TAKING A WIRE
THE WIDTH OF A HAIR

23:08.928 --> 23:11.511
AND MANEUVERING IT THROUGH
THE MOM'S ABDOMEN,

23:11.511 --> 23:12.972
INTO THE UTERUS,

23:12.972 --> 23:14.644
AND THEN THROUGH
THE AMNIOTIC CAVITY,

23:14.644 --> 23:16.816
AND THEN INTO
THE TINY FETUS' CHEST,

23:16.816 --> 23:20.229
INTO AN INSANELY TINY HEART,
TO SAVE A TINY HUMAN.

23:20.229 --> 23:21.230
HM. YAY, YOU.

23:22.822 --> 23:23.943
OK-- Y-- HEY, PULL GENTLY.

23:23.943 --> 23:25.404
I AM. STOP IT.

23:25.404 --> 23:27.406
THINK ABOUT ALL THE SURGERIES
I'LL SAVE YOU FROM HAVING TO DO.

23:27.406 --> 23:29.489
REMIND ME
TO THANK YOU LATER.

23:29.489 --> 23:31.951
NOW, WOULD YOU PLEASE --
MY JOB'S GONNA MAKE
YOUR JOB OBSOLETE.

23:31.951 --> 23:34.123
[ ALARM BEEPING ]
DAMN IT.
OH, ALEX, NO!

23:34.123 --> 23:36.956
Chase: YOU'RE SAYING
WE HAVE TO START THIS
WHOLE ORDEAL OVER AGAIN?

23:36.956 --> 23:39.418
SINCE WE HAD TO REATTACH
LEE'S SUTURES IN THE O.R.,

23:39.418 --> 23:40.920
IT DID SET US BACK
A FEW DAYS.

23:40.920 --> 23:43.342
BUT I ASSURE YOU, IT'S
A MINOR COMPLICATION
OF THE TECHNIQUE.

23:43.342 --> 23:45.134
NOTHING ABOUT THIS
IS MINOR!

23:45.134 --> 23:46.846
NOW IT SOUNDS LIKE
YOU'VE JUST MADE HIM WORSE!

23:46.846 --> 23:49.509
HONEY, MAYBE THIS --
SHE HASN'T HELD HER SON ONCE.

23:49.509 --> 23:50.640
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT THAT'S LIKE FOR HER,

23:50.640 --> 23:51.761
FOR HER TO STAND HERE

23:51.761 --> 23:53.222
AND JUST SEE HIM
COVERED IN TUBES?

23:53.222 --> 23:54.644
SIR, I'M VERY SORRY.

23:54.644 --> 23:56.185
YOU'RE THE ONE WHO SHOULD BE
THE ONE APOLOGIZING.

23:56.185 --> 23:57.396
YOU WERE SUPPOSED TO DO
THE SURGERY,

23:57.396 --> 23:58.728
BUT YOU JUST PASSED IT OFF
TO HIM!

23:58.728 --> 24:00.610
I ASSURE YOU
THAT DR. KAREV --

24:00.610 --> 24:02.942
YEAH, HE'S VERY GOOD.
HE'S "AWESOME." WE REMEMBER.

24:02.942 --> 24:06.826
MY BABY BOY'S CHEST
HAS NOW BEEN CUT INTO TWICE,

24:06.826 --> 24:08.948
SO YOU'LL FORGIVE ME
IF I DON'T SHARE YOUR OPINION.

24:11.871 --> 24:13.623
ALEX, HEY, I'M S--

24:13.623 --> 24:14.664
NO, I'M SORRY.

24:14.664 --> 24:16.415
I'M SORRY FOR NOT TELLING YOU
THIS SOONER.

24:16.415 --> 24:18.788
I NEVER SHOULD HAVE LET
YOU DICTATE A PROCEDURE
I DON'T BELIEVE IN.

24:18.788 --> 24:19.879
THIS IS MY PATIENT,

24:19.879 --> 24:21.881
THIS IS MY SERVICE,
THIS IS MY NICU.

24:21.881 --> 24:24.674
AND LAST TIME I CHECKED,
I WAS THE ATTENDING,
AND YOU WERE A FELLOW,

24:24.674 --> 24:27.176
SO STOP OVERSTEPPING, AND
GET THE HELL OFF MY FLOOR NOW!

24:37.897 --> 24:39.398
Callie:
THIS LESION IS EXTENDING

24:39.398 --> 24:41.270
ALL THE WAY ACROSS
DAVID'S SUBTROCH REGION.

24:41.270 --> 24:42.481
I CAN'T BELIEVE
HE MADE IT THIS FAR

24:42.481 --> 24:43.943
WITHOUT FRACTURING
HIS ENTIRE FEMUR.

24:43.943 --> 24:45.404
HOW'S THE BREAK GOING?

24:45.404 --> 24:46.866
MEREDITH.

24:46.866 --> 24:48.868
I MEAN, DIET.

24:48.868 --> 24:50.780
HOW'S THE DIET GOING?
DIET, RIGHT.

24:50.780 --> 24:54.954
UH, I'M BACK ON TRACK,
I THINK.

24:54.954 --> 24:55.995
DAY 16.

24:55.995 --> 24:57.246
NO MORE LATE-NIGHT BINGES?

24:57.246 --> 24:59.579
WELL, I ALMOST HAD
A, UH, CHEESEBURGER,

24:59.579 --> 25:01.961
BUT THEN I DIDN'T, SO --

25:01.961 --> 25:04.043
THAT WAS ROUGH,
'CAUSE I LIKE CHEESEBURGERS.

25:04.043 --> 25:06.465
[ LAUGHS ]
OH, GOD, I MISS CHEESEBURGERS.

25:06.465 --> 25:09.839
DEREK WANTS A CHEESEBURGER
EVERY SINGLE NIGHT,

25:09.839 --> 25:12.091
AND I TELL HIM HE CAN'T HAVE ONE
TILL THE END OF THE YEAR,

25:12.091 --> 25:14.934
SO HE SHOULD JUST GO
AND SLEEP ON THE COUCH.

25:14.934 --> 25:16.766
HM.
YOU'RE LUCKY.

25:16.766 --> 25:19.398
AT LEAST YOUR DIET HAS
AN END DATE -- 30 DAYS, RIGHT?

25:19.398 --> 25:22.441
IMAGINE HOW GOOD
THAT CHEESEBURGER'S GONNA TASTE

25:22.441 --> 25:24.143
WHEN YOUR DIET'S DONE.
NO.

25:24.143 --> 25:26.235
DID I GO TOO FAR?
NO, NO, NO. LOOK, LOOK.

25:26.235 --> 25:27.907
SEE THAT INFLAMMATION?

25:27.907 --> 25:29.859
THE BLOOD SUPPLY'S
COMPLETELY GONE.

25:29.859 --> 25:31.530
A TOTAL HIP
WON'T SURVIVE IN HERE.

25:31.530 --> 25:33.242
POOR HEALING,
CRAPPY SURGICAL BED,

25:33.242 --> 25:34.784
HIS IMMUNOCOMPROMISED
STATE --

25:34.784 --> 25:36.365
IT'D BE INFECTED
WITHIN A WEEK.

25:36.365 --> 25:38.868
SO, WHAT
DO YOU WANT TO DO?
[ SIGHS ]

25:38.868 --> 25:43.292
Callie: WE REMOVED THE TUMOR
ALONG WITH THE NECROTIC BONE,

25:43.292 --> 25:45.294
AND WE COMPLETELY WASHED OUT
THE AREA.

25:45.294 --> 25:46.876
IT WAS FAIRLY INFLAMED,

25:46.876 --> 25:49.258
SO WE ALSO PLACED
ANTIBIOTIC-LOADED
CEMENT SPACERS.

25:49.258 --> 25:51.801
SO, RIGHT NOW,
HE HAS NO HIP?

25:51.801 --> 25:54.383
H-HOW CAN HE GET OUT OF BED
OR WALK?

25:54.383 --> 25:56.055
HE CAN'T.

25:56.055 --> 25:58.097
THAT EX-FIX I ATTACHED IS
THE ONLY THING

25:58.097 --> 26:00.179
SECURING HIS LEG IN PLACE
TO THE REST OF HIS BODY.

26:00.179 --> 26:02.481
OH, GOD.
WHY DID YOU...

26:02.481 --> 26:04.984
YOU SAID THAT YOU DO THIS
ALL THE TIME.

26:04.984 --> 26:05.895
I AM SO SORRY.

26:05.895 --> 26:07.897
I DIDN'T KNOW HOW MUCH DAMAGE
THERE WOULD BE

26:07.897 --> 26:10.029
UNTIL WE ACTUALLY OPENED
YOUR HUSBAND UP.

26:10.029 --> 26:11.360
Meredith:
THE EX-FIX IS ONLY TEMPORARY.

26:11.360 --> 26:13.112
WE WILL FIND
A PERMANENT SOLUTION.

26:13.112 --> 26:15.785
THE IMPORTANT THING IS
WE GOT THE TUMOR,

26:15.785 --> 26:17.957
AND WE STOPPED IT FROM CAUSING
DAVID ANY MORE PROBLEMS.

26:17.957 --> 26:19.789
I NEED --
I NEED TO BE WITH HIM.

26:19.789 --> 26:20.910
OF COURSE.

26:24.754 --> 26:28.047
OH, GOD,
I'M HAVING THE WORST MONTH.

26:28.047 --> 26:30.129
[ SIGHS ]
I KNOW WHAT WE NEED.

26:30.129 --> 26:32.011
HMM?

26:32.011 --> 26:35.054
OH, YOU ARE SO SMART --
SO SMART.

26:35.054 --> 26:36.926
CAN'T EAT ALL OF THIS.
OH, NO, NO.

26:36.926 --> 26:38.217
[ CHUCKLES ]
WE'LL SPLIT IT.

26:38.217 --> 26:40.099
CHEERS.

26:40.099 --> 26:41.721
AH.

26:48.938 --> 26:50.990
WAIT.
WHAT?

26:50.990 --> 26:52.732
WE COULD SPLIT IT.
WE ARE.

26:52.732 --> 26:55.655
NO, NO, NO. WHAT IF WE --
WHAT IF WE SPLIT IT?

26:55.655 --> 26:57.116
IF YOU WANT THE WHOLE THING,
YOU CAN HAVE THE WHOLE THING.

26:57.116 --> 27:00.199
NO, THE LEG, THE -- FOR DAVID,
THE -- LOOK, IT'S GENIUS.

27:00.199 --> 27:04.623
IF WE TAKE HIS FIBULA BONE
AND WE SPLIT IT INTO TWO PIECES,

27:04.623 --> 27:07.917
WE CAN USE THAT TO BRIDGE THE
GAP FROM THE TUMOR RESECTION.

27:07.917 --> 27:09.749
THE FIBULA WILL STILL HAVE
ITS NATIVE VESSELS

27:09.749 --> 27:10.880
THAT WE CAN ATTACH.

27:10.880 --> 27:13.342
SO, YOU ATTACH THE PEDICLE
TO THE CIRCUMFLEX ARTERY

27:13.342 --> 27:15.174
AND THEN CORE OUT
THE NECROTIC BONE?

27:15.174 --> 27:17.426
YOU DO THAT?
WORKS FOR NON-UNIONS.

27:17.426 --> 27:19.058
I DON'T SEE WHY IT WOULDN'T WORK
FOR A TUMOR.

27:19.058 --> 27:20.850
AND HE STILL GETS TO KEEP
HIS LEG?
YES!

27:20.850 --> 27:21.971
[ LAUGHS ]
HM.

27:21.971 --> 27:23.813
OKAY, WE'RE GONNA NEED
MORE PICKLES.

27:32.902 --> 27:35.034
[ ALARMS BEEPING ]

27:35.034 --> 27:36.906
WE BROKE THE RULES
AGAIN.

27:36.906 --> 27:39.038
SO, YOU HAD SEX?
NO, NO.

27:43.913 --> 27:45.584
WHEN SHE DIDN'T COME HOME,

27:45.584 --> 27:47.336
I THOUGHT SHE WAS SLEEPING
WITH SOMEONE ELSE,

27:47.336 --> 27:50.209
WHICH IS
AGAINST THE RULES,

27:50.209 --> 27:53.422
AND, ALSO, THE IDEA
REALLY, REALLY BUGGED ME.

27:53.422 --> 27:56.095
AND THEN, WHEN I THOUGHT,
WELL, IF SHE'S NOT DOING THAT,

27:56.095 --> 27:57.556
THEN WHAT IF SHE'S NOT OKAY?

27:57.556 --> 27:58.798
'CAUSE THAT BUGGED ME MORE.

27:58.798 --> 28:01.510
SO, I MADE HER TALK TO ME.

28:01.510 --> 28:03.142
SO, I KNOW THAT
WE'RE NOT SUPPOSED TO,

28:03.142 --> 28:04.433
BUT WE STILL LIVE
IN THE SAME HOUSE,

28:04.433 --> 28:05.725
SO I KNOW
WHEN YOU DON'T COME HOME.

28:05.725 --> 28:07.476
OKAY.

28:07.476 --> 28:09.608
AND I KNOW IT'S NONE OF
MY BUSINESS, BUT THERE'S SOFIA,

28:09.608 --> 28:11.270
AND SO, YOU KNOW, IF SOMETHING
WERE TO HAPPEN TO YOU,

28:11.270 --> 28:13.692
I WOULDN'T KNOW WHERE YOU WERE
OR WHO YOU WERE WITH.

28:13.692 --> 28:15.985
I WAS HERE.
[ SIGHS ] DON'T.

28:15.985 --> 28:17.987
OKAY? 'CAUSE I SEARCHED
THE CALL RECORDS FOR YOUR NAME.

28:17.987 --> 28:20.199
OH, SO YOU STALKED ME?
I WAS WORRIED.

28:20.199 --> 28:22.872
I WAS AT DINNER
WITH GREY.

28:22.872 --> 28:24.413
WE CAME UP WITH A FIX
FOR A PATIENT,

28:24.413 --> 28:25.704
AND WE CAME BACK HERE
TO WORK ON IT.

28:25.704 --> 28:27.586
WITH MEREDITH?
YES. WHAT?

28:27.586 --> 28:29.208
WHAT,
YOU THINK SOMETHING HA--

28:29.208 --> 28:32.251
I WAS WITH MEREDITH GREY,
AND SUDDENLY, IT WAS 3:00 A.M.

28:32.251 --> 28:34.794
I DIDN'T WANT TO DRIVE HOME,
SO I SLEPT IN AN ON-CALL ROOM.

28:34.794 --> 28:36.715
[ SIGHS ]

28:36.715 --> 28:38.888
SHE WAS JEALOUS --

28:38.888 --> 28:43.392
LIKE, IRRATIONALLY,
OBVIOUSLY JEALOUS.

28:43.392 --> 28:45.975
DO YOU KNOW HOW THAT FEELS,
TO HAVE SOMEONE BE JEALOUS,

28:45.975 --> 28:47.897
TO BE WORRIED
THAT YOU'RE CHEATING?

28:47.897 --> 28:49.648
IT FEELS NICE.

28:49.648 --> 28:50.980
[ LAUGHS ]

28:50.980 --> 28:52.812
WELL,
IT'S NOT THE HEALTHIEST --

28:52.812 --> 28:54.904
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO,
I JUST MEAN, SHE WAS --
SHE WAS WORRIED ABOUT ME.

28:54.904 --> 28:56.906
SHE -- SHE CARED.

28:58.948 --> 29:01.570
DOES THAT MEAN THIS THING
MIGHT ACTUALLY BE WORKING?

29:08.577 --> 29:09.789
[ SAW WHIRS ]

29:09.789 --> 29:11.831
Callie: ALL RIGHT,
JUST GIVE ME A FEW MINUTES,

29:11.831 --> 29:14.673
AND I WILL HAVE VIABLE
AND STRUCTURALLY SOUND
BONE COMING YOUR WAY.

29:14.673 --> 29:17.086
THERE'S NO SIGN OF INFECTION
IN THE SUBTROCH REGION,

29:17.086 --> 29:18.757
SO THE ANTIBIOTIC SPACERS
WORKED.

29:18.757 --> 29:21.590
HOW'S THE BLOOD SUPPLY?
OH, IT'S FREAKING AMAZING.

29:21.590 --> 29:24.183
ALL RIGHT, WE'LL USE A
PORTION OF THE PERONEAL ARTERY
AND ITS ADJOINING VEINS.

29:24.183 --> 29:25.724
OKAY,
READY WHEN YOU ARE.

29:25.724 --> 29:27.096
ALL RIGHT, AFTER I FINISH
THE FEMORAL CANAL,

29:27.096 --> 29:28.767
WE WILL INCORPORATE
THE FIBULA

29:28.767 --> 29:31.270
INTO A PLATE-AND-SCREW CONSTRUCT
TO SPAN THE DEFECT.

29:31.270 --> 29:34.063
AND WE'LL DO THE VESSEL
ANASTOMOSIS WITH AN 8-0 NYLON,

29:34.063 --> 29:35.774
AND WE'LL DO
SIMPLE, INTERRUPTED SUTURES.

29:35.774 --> 29:37.486
THEN WE WILL CHECK
FOR LEAKS

29:37.486 --> 29:39.238
AND PATCH ANY WE FIND
WITH FAT GRAFTS.

29:39.238 --> 29:41.200
HOPEFULLY, WE'LL HAVE
THE PATIENT WEIGHT-BEARING
WITHIN A COUPLE OF WEEKS.

29:41.200 --> 29:42.781
ANY QUESTIONS?
Nurse: DR. TORRES.

29:42.781 --> 29:43.953
YES?
WHEN YOU'RE DONE IN HERE,

29:43.953 --> 29:46.826
THEY'RE ASKING
THAT YOU GO DOWN TO THE E.R.
WHY?

29:46.826 --> 29:49.208
PUSH 50 OF FENTANYL.

29:49.208 --> 29:50.409
WHAT HAPPENED?

29:50.409 --> 29:51.961
Stephanie:
PARAMEDICS SAID SHE RAN HER CAR

29:51.961 --> 29:54.373
STRAIGHT THROUGH A GUARD RAIL
AND INTO A TREE.
SHE'S LUCKY TO BE ALIVE.

29:54.373 --> 29:55.584
Emily:
[ Weakly ] MAKE IT STOP.

29:55.584 --> 29:58.007
LET ME DIE.
PLEASE, MAKE IT STOP.

29:58.007 --> 29:59.718
DID SHE DO IT
ON PURPOSE?

29:59.718 --> 30:01.630
WELL, CAN'T GET ANYTHING
OUT OF HER RIGHT NOW
THAT MAKES SENSE.

30:03.552 --> 30:06.345
OH, GOD.

30:08.057 --> 30:09.889
WAIT, CALLIE.

30:09.889 --> 30:11.640
WHAT'S THE STORY
WITH THIS GIRL?

30:11.640 --> 30:14.643
[ Voice breaking ] I REPAIRED
HER ARM FRACTURE A MONTH AGO,

30:14.643 --> 30:16.605
BUT SHE'S STILL
IN HORRIBLE PAIN,

30:16.605 --> 30:17.937
AND I-I CAN'T FIND
ANYTHING WRONG WITH HER.

30:17.937 --> 30:19.438
THERE'S NOTHING WRONG
WITH HER.

30:19.438 --> 30:20.819
I DON'T KNOW
IF IT'S REFERRED PAIN

30:20.819 --> 30:22.862
OR SOME KIND OF WEIRD
PHANTOM LIMB, BUT...
OKAY, LISTEN.

30:22.862 --> 30:24.243
...I THINK SHE JUST TRIED
TO KILL HERSELF.

30:24.243 --> 30:25.784
AND DON'T TELL ME IT'S NOT
MY FAULT, BECAUSE IT IS.

30:25.784 --> 30:26.906
IT'S MY FAULT.

30:26.906 --> 30:28.657
IT'S MY FAULT
THAT I CAN'T STOP THE PAIN.

30:28.657 --> 30:29.748
STOP.

30:31.500 --> 30:33.502
THERE, SEE?
YOU SEE THAT?

30:33.502 --> 30:35.294
THOSE TEENY THINGS?
BARELY.

30:35.294 --> 30:36.876
THEY'RE FLUID-FILLED CYSTS.

30:36.876 --> 30:39.298
EMILY'S ARM INJURY RIPPED
THE NERVES FROM HER SPINAL CORD,

30:39.298 --> 30:41.630
CAUSING HER TO DEVELOP
SPINAL EPILEPSY.

30:41.630 --> 30:44.013
[ SIGHS ]
INSTEAD OF HAVING SEIZURES,
SHE DEVELOPS THESE --

30:44.013 --> 30:45.464
SHOCKS OF PAIN.

30:45.464 --> 30:47.887
IS THERE ANY WAY TO --
FIX IT? YEAH. IT'S RISKY.

30:47.887 --> 30:49.638
I HAVE TO BURN
THE NERVE ENDINGS OF HER SPINE

30:49.638 --> 30:51.850
TO STOP THE COMMUNICATION OF
THE PAIN SIGNALS TO HER ARM.

30:51.850 --> 30:53.472
OH. CAN YOU DO IT?

30:53.472 --> 30:55.814
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

30:55.814 --> 30:57.186
[ LAUGHS ]

30:57.186 --> 30:58.397
Dr. Herman: SO...

30:58.397 --> 31:00.940
ADDISON MONTGOMERY
WITH A TODDLER.

31:00.940 --> 31:02.321
OH, YEAH.

31:02.321 --> 31:05.154
HENRY HAS COMPLETELY DESTROYED
HER WHITE WALLS AND CARPETS.

31:05.154 --> 31:06.745
HE'S CURRENTLY
INTO DRAWING

31:06.745 --> 31:09.949
AND SPILLING
AND SMEARING.

31:09.949 --> 31:11.370
YEAH, WELL, LOOKS LIKE
WE WON'T SEE HER

31:11.370 --> 31:12.952
ON THE CONFERENCE CIRCUIT
FOR A LITTLE WHILE.

31:12.952 --> 31:14.833
UM, I DIDN'T KNOW
THAT YOU KNEW ADDISON, TOO.

31:14.833 --> 31:15.955
DID YOU FINISH ROUNDING?

31:15.955 --> 31:17.416
YES.

31:17.416 --> 31:19.128
UM, Y-YEAH.

31:19.128 --> 31:20.960
I W-WANTED TO TELL YOU
THAT MS. CAIN GAVE CONSENT
TO HER VALVULOPLASTY.

31:20.960 --> 31:23.923
UM, SHOULD I SCHEDULE IT?
YEAH. DAY AFTER NEXT.

31:23.923 --> 31:25.925
AND YOU'RE LEADING THIS ONE,
ROBBINS.

31:25.925 --> 31:27.426
GRAHAM WILL ASSIST
AND HOLD THE NEEDLES.

31:27.426 --> 31:28.427
I'LL OBSERVE.

31:28.427 --> 31:29.768
YOU BE READY THIS TIME.

31:29.768 --> 31:30.889
YES, MA'AM.

31:33.892 --> 31:36.355
DID YOU NEED
SOMETHING ELSE?

31:37.816 --> 31:39.688
N-NO.

31:41.941 --> 31:44.903
SO, HENRY --
THAT'S A CUTE NAME, THOUGH.
IT'S CUTE.

31:44.903 --> 31:48.117
HEY, UM,
HOW'S HE DOING?

31:48.117 --> 31:49.788
CAN I SEE
THE MOST RECENT GAPOGRAM?

31:49.788 --> 31:52.331
UH, I'M NOT SURE
THAT I SHOULD.

31:54.623 --> 31:55.794
I'M LEAVING, OKAY?

31:55.794 --> 31:57.416
IT'S YOUR -- YOUR PATIENT,
YOUR NICU,

31:57.416 --> 31:59.959
YOUR TERRITORY,
SO I'M GONE.

32:03.963 --> 32:05.844
Derek:
OKAY, CORD'S EXPOSED.

32:05.844 --> 32:08.677
I'M ABOUT TO SEND DOWN
THE RADIOFREQUENCY PROBE.

32:08.677 --> 32:11.850
I NEVER EVEN THOUGHT TO LOOK
PAST THE ARM, AND NOW [SIGHS]

32:11.850 --> 32:14.473
I MAY HAVE BLOWN HER CHANCES
AT CULINARY SCHOOL --

32:14.473 --> 32:16.015
GOTTEN HER HOOKED ON PAIN MEDS,
TO BOOT.

32:16.015 --> 32:18.017
IT'S NOT YOUR FAULT.

32:18.017 --> 32:19.938
NO, THIS -- THIS PROBLEM
GOES MUCH DEEPER

32:19.938 --> 32:23.192
THAN ANYTHING YOU COULD HAVE
SEEN OR COULD HAVE CONTROLLED.

32:23.192 --> 32:25.114
IT'S NOT YOUR FAULT
AT ALL.

32:25.114 --> 32:30.829
♪ WHY WOULD I SPEND
THE REST OF MY DAYS UNHAPPY? ♪

32:30.829 --> 32:34.953
♪ WHY WOULD I SPEND
THE REST OF THIS YEAR ALONE? ♪
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

32:34.953 --> 32:37.876
♪ WHEN I CAN GO THERAPY ♪

32:37.876 --> 32:40.839
♪ WHEN I CAN GO THERAPY ♪

32:40.839 --> 32:46.675
♪ WHEN I CAN GO THERAPY
TWO TIMES A DAY ♪

32:46.675 --> 32:52.971
♪ WHY WOULD I SPEND THE REST
OF THIS WEEK SO BITTER? ♪

32:52.971 --> 32:58.397
♪ AND ALL THAT LISTENING
IS MAKING YOU BITTER, TOO ♪

32:58.397 --> 33:01.440
♪ WHEN I CAN GO THERAPY ♪

33:01.440 --> 33:04.193
♪ WHEN I CAN GO THERAPY ♪

33:04.193 --> 33:10.529
♪ WHEN I CAN GO THERAPY
TWO TIMES A DAY ♪

33:10.529 --> 33:13.492
♪ SOMEONE HELP ME
TURN AROUND ♪
CALLIOPE. I --
Callie: SHH.

33:13.492 --> 33:16.665
♪ I'M A VICTIM ♪
I NEED --
I NEED TO PRACTICE.

33:16.665 --> 33:18.577
♪ HATE THE SOUND
OF MY OWN VOICE ♪
NO TALKING.

33:18.577 --> 33:19.878
♪ TURN IT DOWN ♪
RULES.

33:19.878 --> 33:22.501
♪ AND ALL I DO IS AGGRAVATION ♪

33:22.501 --> 33:26.835
♪ WHY WOULD I SPEND
THE REST OF MY DAYS SO BITTER? ♪

33:26.835 --> 33:28.927
TOMORROW'S THE LAST DAY.

33:28.927 --> 33:30.889
♪ AND ALL THAT LISTENING
IS MAKING YOU BITTER, TOO ♪

33:30.889 --> 33:32.891
SO? CLOSE ENOUGH,
RIGHT?
YEAH.

33:32.891 --> 33:35.304
♪ WHEN I CAN GO THERAPY ♪
OH, WHAT IF SHE MAKES US
START OVER AGAIN?

33:35.304 --> 33:37.056
♪ WHEN I CAN GO THERAPY ♪
SO, WHAT IF
WE DON'T TELL HER?

33:37.056 --> 33:39.348
OH.
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

33:39.348 --> 33:42.981
♪ WHEN I CAN GO THERAPY
TWO TIMES A DAY ♪
[ BOTH MOANING ]

33:49.778 --> 33:51.570
HEY, UM,
I JUST GOT YOUR PAGE.

33:51.570 --> 33:53.612
I THOUGHT THE CAIN VALVULOPLASTY
WAS SCHEDULED FOR TOMORROW.

33:53.612 --> 33:55.204
IT WAS.

33:55.204 --> 33:56.825
ULTRASOUND SHOWED
MILD FETAL HYDROPS.

33:56.825 --> 33:58.747
SO NOT ONLY DOES
IT HAVE TO HAPPEN TODAY...

33:58.747 --> 33:59.868
IT HAS TO HAPPEN
RIGHT NOW.

34:01.540 --> 34:03.752
YOU READY?

34:06.335 --> 34:07.586
READY.

34:07.586 --> 34:09.468
NEEDLE, PLEASE?

34:16.014 --> 34:17.436
STOP.

34:18.887 --> 34:20.058
WHAT'S WRONG?

34:20.058 --> 34:21.310
I SHOULD BE ASKING YOU
THAT.

34:21.310 --> 34:23.392
I'M SORRY.
I DON'T FOLLOW.

34:23.392 --> 34:24.523
YOU HESITATED.

34:24.523 --> 34:25.854
YOU STEADIED YOUR HAND.
I WATCHED YOU.

34:25.854 --> 34:27.025
NO, NO, I'M FINE.

34:27.025 --> 34:28.647
ARE YOU NERVOUS?
NO.

34:28.647 --> 34:30.279
I MEAN --
OF COURSE I AM, BUT --

34:30.279 --> 34:32.951
WHY? WHY ARE YOU NERVOUS?
ARE YOU WELL-RESTED?

34:32.951 --> 34:35.364
YES, DR. HERMAN.
BUT YOU'RE PREPARED, RIGHT?

34:35.364 --> 34:36.745
YOU STUDIED
THE FETAL ECHO,

34:36.745 --> 34:37.906
YOU MEMORIZED
THE MEASUREMENTS,

34:37.906 --> 34:39.288
YOU PRACTICED THE ANGLES?

34:39.288 --> 34:41.200
DO YOU KNOW EXACTLY
HOW FAR TO INSERT THE NEEDLE,

34:41.200 --> 34:43.582
AT WHICH POINT TO DEPLOY
THE WIRE, INFLATE THE BALLOON?

34:43.582 --> 34:45.544
I DO. I THINK I --
DO YOU THINK, OR YOU KNOW?

34:45.544 --> 34:47.666
I KNOW. I KNOW.
I KNOW!

34:49.878 --> 34:51.840
GRAHAM, TRADE PLACES
WITH ROBBINS.

34:51.840 --> 34:53.091
ABSOLUTELY.

34:53.091 --> 34:55.344
DR. HERMAN, I --
IT'S FINE.

34:55.344 --> 34:57.806
WE'VE JUST LOST
SOME VALUABLE TIME.

35:01.850 --> 35:03.852
[ SIGHS ]

35:03.852 --> 35:06.985
[ WOMAN TALKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER P.A. ]

35:06.985 --> 35:08.437
HI.
Woman: HI.

35:08.437 --> 35:10.108
WHERE YOU BEEN?
VACATION.

35:12.861 --> 35:15.784
RIGHT IN HERE IS FINE.

35:15.784 --> 35:17.906
OH. HI.

35:19.698 --> 35:21.200
LET ME JUST EXPLAIN.

35:21.200 --> 35:22.791
DO YOU KNOW HOW MANY
FETAL SURGEONS THERE ARE

35:22.791 --> 35:24.203
WEST OF
THE MISSISSIPPI RIVER?

35:24.203 --> 35:26.295
FIVE.
THERE ARE FIVE OF US.

35:26.295 --> 35:28.797
AND I NEED A SIXTH, ROBBINS,
SO I PICKED YOU.

35:28.797 --> 35:31.670
OUT OF EVERYONE,
I HANDPICKED YOU.

35:31.670 --> 35:33.842
AND YOU ARE
LETTING ME DOWN.

35:33.842 --> 35:36.014
I'M NOT JUST QUESTIONING
YOUR ABILITIES.

35:36.014 --> 35:37.386
NOW I'M QUESTIONING MINE.

35:37.386 --> 35:39.558
I THOUGHT
YOU HAD SOMETHING.

35:39.558 --> 35:41.059
I THOUGHT
YOU WERE SPECIAL.

35:41.059 --> 35:43.021
YOU'RE THE CHIEF
OF PEDIATRIC SURGERY.

35:43.021 --> 35:45.764
YOU'RE A MEMBER OF THE BOARD,
WELL-RESPECTED AMONG PEERS.

35:45.764 --> 35:48.817
I THOUGHT YOU WOULD BE BETTER
AND IN LESS TIME.

35:48.817 --> 35:51.650
BUT TODAY?
TODAY, YOU EMBARRASSED ME.

35:51.650 --> 35:55.033
TODAY, YOU WERE UNPREPARED
FOR THE SECOND TIME.

35:55.033 --> 35:56.905
SO I MIGHT
HAVE TO RETHINK THIS,

35:56.905 --> 35:59.278
BECAUSE YOU MIGHT NOT HAVE
WHAT IT TAKES HERE.

35:59.278 --> 36:00.949
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU.

36:00.949 --> 36:02.581
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT KIND OF DEMONS YOU HAVE.

36:02.581 --> 36:05.784
BUT I CAN TELL YOU THAT YOU ARE
BEHIND IN THIS FELLOWSHIP,

36:05.784 --> 36:07.916
AND I DON'T HAVE TIME
FOR YOU TO CATCH UP.

36:07.916 --> 36:11.420
I DON'T HAVE TIME
FOR THREE STRIKES.

36:11.420 --> 36:14.713
SOMETHING LIKE THIS
HAPPENS AGAIN, YOU'RE OUT.

36:25.224 --> 36:27.726
ANY PAIN?
NO.

36:27.726 --> 36:29.187
IT'S ALL GONE.

36:29.187 --> 36:30.309
WHAT ABOUT YOUR ARM?

36:30.309 --> 36:31.900
NOTHING.

36:31.900 --> 36:34.022
[ CHUCKLES ]

36:34.022 --> 36:36.365
WHEN MY CAR HIT THAT TREE,

36:36.365 --> 36:38.777
THE FIRST THOUGHT
THAT CAME INTO MY HEAD WAS,

36:38.777 --> 36:42.741
"AT LEAST IT'S OVER" --
NO MORE PAIN,

36:42.741 --> 36:44.743
NO MORE SWALLOWING
A BUNCH OF PILLS,

36:44.743 --> 36:46.375
TRYING TO MAKE IT STOP,

36:46.375 --> 36:48.377
NO MORE CRYING
ON MY COUCH

36:48.377 --> 36:51.290
WATCHING THOSE STUPID,
CHEESY COOKING SHOWS,

36:51.290 --> 36:53.502
THINKING ABOUT FOOD
I'D NEVER MAKE.

36:53.502 --> 36:56.795
AND, GOD, STOP FEELING SORRY
FOR MYSELF.

36:56.795 --> 36:58.927
[ SIGHS ]

36:58.927 --> 37:00.889
THANK YOU.

37:00.889 --> 37:05.844
I FINALLY FEEL LIKE
I MIGHT ACTUALLY SURVIVE THIS.

37:05.844 --> 37:07.896
[ CHUCKLES ]

37:14.192 --> 37:16.485
Meredith:
THAT'S ALL YOU, YOU KNOW.

37:18.817 --> 37:21.990
WELL, HE'S GOT A TOUGH ROAD
AHEAD -- MONTHS OF P.T. --

37:21.990 --> 37:23.952
BUT THAT GRAFT SHOULD LAST HIM
FOR YEARS.

37:23.952 --> 37:25.824
HOPEFULLY, THIS IS THE BEGINNING
OF THE END FOR HIM.

37:25.824 --> 37:26.825
SO, WHAT ABOUT YOU?

37:26.825 --> 37:28.126
IT'S DAY 30, ISN'T IT?

37:28.126 --> 37:29.918
[ SIGHS ] IT IS.
[ LAUGHS ]

37:29.918 --> 37:31.750
DAY 30.

37:31.750 --> 37:34.873
UH, I AM...WEIRDLY NERVOUS.

37:34.873 --> 37:38.136
I MEAN, I FEEL GOOD,
BUT I -- I DON'T KNOW.

37:38.136 --> 37:40.138
IT FEELS LIKE COMING BACK
FROM SOMEWHERE.

37:40.138 --> 37:41.800
WELL, EVEN THOUGH
THE DIET'S OVER,

37:41.800 --> 37:44.012
I'M ALWAYS UP
FOR CHEESEBURGERS AND TEQUILA.

37:44.012 --> 37:45.344
OH.

37:45.344 --> 37:47.095
ACTUAL CHEESEBURGERS.

37:47.095 --> 37:48.687
[ LAUGHS ]

37:48.687 --> 37:50.849
Callie:
ONCE THE CHAOS SUBSIDES,

37:50.849 --> 37:53.101
WE HAVE TO GO BACK...
[ SIGHS ]

37:53.101 --> 37:55.774
...TAKE ANOTHER LOOK.

37:55.774 --> 37:59.488
WE HAVE TO ASK OURSELVES...

38:02.491 --> 38:04.783
...CAN THIS BODY
BE PUT BACK TOGETHER?

38:04.783 --> 38:07.666
WE WERE ABLE TO PUT
LEE'S ESOPHAGUS BACK TOGETHER,

38:07.666 --> 38:09.788
AND I ASSURE YOU,
IT'S STRONGER THAN EVER.

38:09.788 --> 38:13.412
THANK YOU [SNIFFLES]
SO MUCH.

38:13.412 --> 38:18.176
IF WE'VE DONE OUR JOBS RIGHT,
IT CAN.

38:18.176 --> 38:21.470
WE STOP THE BLEEDING.

38:21.470 --> 38:22.761
[ SIGHS ]

38:22.761 --> 38:26.635
WE SEW UP THE DAMAGE.

38:26.635 --> 38:29.348
WE MAKE THE BODY WHOLE AGAIN.

38:29.348 --> 38:32.100
[ SIGHS ]

38:32.100 --> 38:35.894
[ ALARMS BEEPING ]

38:35.894 --> 38:38.276
[ THUNDER RUMBLES ]
I UNDERSTAND
WHY WE DID THIS.

38:38.276 --> 38:42.401
YOU KNOW, IT WAS TO MAKE US
STRONGER, TO MAKE US BETTER.

38:42.401 --> 38:43.942
[ RAIN PATTERING ]
AND IT DID.

38:43.942 --> 38:45.944
I MEAN,
I FEEL LIKE IT REALLY DID.

38:45.944 --> 38:48.617
IT TOOK A LONG TIME,

38:48.617 --> 38:51.790
AND IT WAS PAINFUL,
AND IT SUCKED,

38:51.790 --> 38:56.044
BUT...WE'VE COME
A LONG WAY.

38:56.044 --> 38:59.217
AND I KNOW THAT
WE HAVE FURTHER TO GO, BUT...

38:59.217 --> 39:02.721
I LOVE YOU, CALLIOPE.

39:02.721 --> 39:04.963
I LOVE YOU.

39:04.963 --> 39:08.637
[ CRIES ]
LIFE WITHOUT YOU
TERRIFIES ME.

39:08.637 --> 39:11.970
AND THE WORLD IS JUST MAKING
LESS AND LESS SENSE,

39:11.970 --> 39:14.523
AND, LIKE, I DON'T KNOW
WHAT I'M DOING AT WORK ANYMORE,

39:14.523 --> 39:17.476
BUT THE THING THAT I NEED
IS MY ANCHOR.

39:17.476 --> 39:18.687
IT'S YOU.

39:18.687 --> 39:20.939
I NEED YOU.

39:20.939 --> 39:23.782
AND YOU'RE THE ONLY THING
THAT I WILL EVER NEED.

39:23.782 --> 39:28.987
AND I'M SO GLAD
THAT THIS BREAK IS OVER.

39:28.987 --> 39:31.830
[ SOBS ]

39:31.830 --> 39:34.833
[ THUNDER RUMBLES ]

39:34.833 --> 39:37.295
[ SOBBING ]

39:37.295 --> 39:40.839
[ BREATHING DEEPLY ]

39:45.424 --> 39:50.849
THE LAST 30 DAYS
HAVE TAUGHT ME SO MUCH.

39:52.811 --> 39:54.352
AND ALL I WANTED
WHEN WE FIRST CAME HERE

39:54.352 --> 39:56.775
WAS TO KNOW
THAT WE WOULD LEAVE TOGETHER.

39:59.227 --> 40:01.980
BUT FROM THE MINUTE I SAT DOWN,
I COULD FEEL IT.

40:01.980 --> 40:05.073
I FELT LIKE
I WAS GONNA BE SUFFOCATED.

40:05.073 --> 40:07.696
[ THUNDER RUMBLES ]

40:10.739 --> 40:12.951
[ SIGHS ]

40:12.951 --> 40:16.745
THE LAST SEVERAL WEEKS,

40:16.745 --> 40:19.668
I HAVE LAUGHED MORE,
I HAVE DONE MORE,

40:19.668 --> 40:22.961
I HAVE ENJOYED MYSELF MORE,
THAN...

40:22.961 --> 40:25.674
[SOBS]

40:25.674 --> 40:27.846
...AND I FINALLY FEEL FREE.

40:30.759 --> 40:33.852
AND BY BEING FREE,

40:33.852 --> 40:37.816
I CAN SEE NOW THAT
CONSTANTLY TRYING TO FIX US

40:37.816 --> 40:40.268
IS THE THING THAT'S BEEN
KILLING ME SLOWLY.

40:43.732 --> 40:45.944
AND I DON'T WANT TO
DO IT ANYMORE.

40:45.944 --> 40:48.657
I DON'T WANT TO FIX IT
OR FIX US ANYMORE.

40:51.830 --> 40:56.164
MAYBE INSTEAD OF LOVING YOU
SO HARD, I SHOULD...

40:56.164 --> 40:59.538
I SHOULD BE MYSELF
FOR A WHILE.

41:02.380 --> 41:05.844
I SHOULD LOVE ME,

41:05.844 --> 41:06.845
AND YOU SHOULD LOVE YOU,

41:06.845 --> 41:10.298
AND TOGETHER WE LOVE SOFIA,
RATHER THAN...

41:18.767 --> 41:22.190
I WANT SO MUCH FOR YOU,
ARIZONA.

41:22.190 --> 41:24.903
FOR BOTH OF US.

41:27.526 --> 41:29.988
SO MUCH MORE THAN THIS.

41:31.530 --> 41:34.823
MORE THAN BEING STUCK
WITH SOMEONE WHO FEELS STUCK.

41:39.618 --> 41:41.830
I WANT YOU
TO FEEL FREE, TOO.

41:41.830 --> 41:43.712
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

41:43.712 --> 41:45.674
[ THUNDER RUMBLING ]

41:49.888 --> 41:53.592
BUT NO MATTER
HOW HARD WE TRY...

42:02.480 --> 42:05.564
[ THUNDER CRASHES ]
...WE HAVE TO REALIZE...

42:09.527 --> 42:12.651
[ SIGHS ]

42:12.651 --> 42:15.363
...SOME THINGS...

42:15.363 --> 42:17.996
JUST CAN'T BE FIXED.
